<HL>
   Ohio Edison Gets Rate Increase
</HL>
<DATE>
08/17/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A2
</SO>
<CO>
   OEC
</CO>
<IN>
ELECTRIC UTILITIES (ELC)
</IN>
<LP>
   COLUMBUS, Ohio -- The Public Utilities Commission of Ohio
granted Ohio Edison Co. a rate increase of 8.5%, or about
$142.3 million, less than the utility's request for a boost
of about $216 million.
   The commission said the typical Ohio Edison customer using
500 kilowatts an hour of electricity now pays about $57.23 a
month. Under the increase, this will rise to $62.38 a month,
the commission estimated.
</LP>
