<HL>
   New Securities Issues
</HL>
<DATE>
08/17/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C17
</SO>
<CO>
   ONE EUROP SPC J.YMT
</CO>
<IN>
BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)
</IN>
<LP>
   The following were among yesterday's offerings and
pricings in U.S. and non-U.S. capital markets, with terms and
syndicate manager, as compiled by Dow Jones Capital Markets
Report.
                                                                                                       

                         CORPORATES
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   Banc One Corp. -- $200 million of 10% subordinated notes
due Aug. 15, 2010, priced at 97.875 to yield 10.25%. The
noncallable notes were priced at a spread of 140 basis points
above the Treasury's 30-year bond. Rated single-A-2 by
Moody's Investors Service Inc. and double-A-minus by Standard
&amp; Poor's Corp., the issue will be sold through underwriters
led by Salomon Brothers Inc.
   Security Pacific Corp. -- $100 million of 8.85% senior
notes due Aug. 15, 1993, priced at 99.955 to yield 8.866%.
The noncallable notes were priced at 67 basis points above
the Treasury's three-year note. Rated single-A-1 by Moody's
and double-A-minus by S&amp;P, the issue will be sold through
underwriters led by Merrill Lynch Capital Markets.
                                                                                                       

                         MUNICIPAL
                                                                                                       

   Metropolitan Seattle -- $100 million of municipality sewer
revenue bonds, Series S, due Jan. 1, 1993-2013 and 2030, via
a Merrill Lynch Capital Markets group. The bonds are rated
single-A-1/double-A-minus. Current interest serial bonds are
priced to yield from 6% in 1993 to 7.40% in 2012 and 2013.
Term bonds due in 2030 with a 7 3/8% coupon are priced to
yield 7.45%.
                                                                                                       

                         EUROBONDS
                                                                                                       

   Yamato Transport Co. -- $230 million of Eurobonds due Aug.
13, 1994, with equity-purchase warrants indicating a 5%
coupon at par, via Nikko Securities Co. Each $10,000 bond
carries two warrants, exercisable from Sept. 13, 1990,
through Aug. 9, 1994, to buy shares at an expected premium of
2 1/2% to the closing price when terms are fixed Wednesday.
Fees 2 1/4.
   Nord LB Finance Curacao N.V. (West German parent) -- 150
million marks of dual-coupon floating rate notes at par due
Sept. 18, 1997, via Norddeutsche Landesbank Girozentrale.
Coupon is six-month London interbank offered rate plus 0.50
point for first two years and 16% less six-month Libor for
the final five years. First Libor fixing is Sept. 14.
Guaranteed by Norddeutsche Landesbank. Fees 0.30.
   Skopbank (Finland) -- 10 billion yen of 7 1/2% Eurobonds
due Dec. 11, 1997, priced at 101 7/8 to yield 7 1/2% after
full fees via Fuji International Finance Ltd. Fees 1 7/8.
</TEXT>
