<LP>
   LOS ANGELES -- American Health Properties Inc. said it
completed a $21.6 million purchase of two Florida properties,
Retreat Psychiatric Hospital and Anclote Manor, from American
Medical Holdings Inc.
   American Health Properties said the transaction marks the
first stage of its purchase of American Medical's
five-hospital psychiatric division for a total purchase price
of about $72 million. "We expect to complete the acquisition
of the remaining three properties, located in California and
Massachusetts, during the third quarter of 1990," said Robert
L. B. Diener, president and chief operating officer of the
real estate investment trust.
