<HL>
   Business Brief -- Toshiba Corp.:
   West German Unit to Lift
   Laptop Computer Output
</HL>
<DATE>
08/17/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B5C
</SO>
<CO>
   J.TOS
</CO>
<LP>
   Toshiba Corp. of Japan will double production of laptop
personal computers at its West German unit by October, half a
year earlier than initially planned, to meet surging demand
in Europe, a company official said.
   Toshiba Europa G.m.b.H., the West German unit, began
producing 5,000 laptops a month at a new 25 million-mark
($15.9 million) factory in Regensburg, Bavaria, last April,
with plans for monthly production of 10,000 units within a
year, a target that was moved up six months.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The company is exporting from Japan that part of European
demand that can't be supplied locally.
   Toshiba holds a 38% share of the European laptop market.
It is producing three laptop computer models of its T-series,
compatible with International Business Corp. machines, with
plans to begin producing an additional model. It also is
considering producing book-type personal computers at the
West German facility.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
