</CO>
<IN>
STEEL MANUFACTURERS (STL)
</IN>
<LP>
   OTTAWA -- Canadian steel ingot production totaled 165,257
metric tons in the week ended last Saturday, down 5.8% from
175,432 tons in the preceding week and down 42% from 284,207
tons a year earlier, Statistics Canada, a federal agency,
said. A metric ton is equal to about 2,204.6 pounds.
   For this year through last Saturday, production totaled
8,622,444 metric tons, down 11% from 9,736,519 tons a year
earlier.
</LP>
