   Dress Barn Inc. said directors authorized a buy-back of
about 10% of shares outstanding in an attempt to boost the
share price of the discount women's apparel retailer.
   The company, which is based in Stamford, Conn., said the
board authorized the purchase of as many as two million
shares. "We believe the stock had gone far below where it
should be," said Elliot Jaffe, Dress Barn's chairman and
chief executive officer.
